Police are investigating a case of murder following the discovery of a woman&#8217;s body at her Eversdal home in Durbanville. CAPE TOWN - Police are investigating a case of murder following the discovery of a woman s body at her Eversdal home in Durbanville.The circumstances around her death earlier this week are not yet clear.The police s Frederick Van Wyk says no arrests have been made. We can confirm that a case of murder has been opened for investigation. According to our report on 9 May on Sondal Street in Eversdal, our members attended to a complaint at the address. On their arrival they found a body of a 53-year-old woman on the floor. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)